videomode
=========
Commandline tool to switch the videomode on an SGI Impact board
between a user defined default mode and 
800x600 60Hz, 2 channels (the glasstron stereo mode!).
This tool switches the videomode and restarts the X server.
Unfortunately there is NO way to avoid the X restart because the 'special 2
channel mode' has other visuals.

Instructions:
-------------
Compile videomode.cxx (just type make)

su to root and do:
chown root.sys videomode
chmod 4711 videomode
echo "cmb/2@800x600_60_ext" >/var/X11/Xvc/2@800x600_60_ext
echo "1280x1024_76" >/var/X11/Xvc/default
exit

If you have/need/want a different default videomode on your SGI box simply
substitute the 1280x1024_76 string with your default mode.

Usage:
------
videomode --glasstron | -g    :   switch to 2x800x600 60Hz (glasstron) mode
videomode --normal    | -n    :   switch back to standard video mode

Questions? Drop me a note at hesina@cg.tuwien.ac.at
